    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Bay Shore station, a stop on the Montauk Branch of the Long Island Rail Road, connects the community to New York City.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        17
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bay_Shore%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "North Bay Shore was originally part of the larger South Bay Shore community before becoming its own census‑designated place.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.wisdomlib.org/cities/north-bay-shore-23804"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The town’s name simply describes its location beside the Great South Bay, a common naming style for U.S. settlements.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.wisdomlib.org/cities/north-bay-shore-23804"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Bay Shore sits on Long Island’s South Shore, directly abutting the Great South Bay and offering waterfront views.",
